    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301702" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Be careful when removing the mainshaft assembly as the sliding clutch on the end can slip off the
            mainshaft. Reverse gear is also free and can fall off the shaft.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear retaining snap ring from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301748">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301748" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301748" filename="../figg13/G1301748.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Reverse Gear Retaining Strap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the mainshaft reverse gear as far to the rear as possible and remove reverse gear I.D.
                snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301748">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the reverse gear forward and against the next gear, engaging the mainshaft sliding
                clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301749">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301749" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301749" filename="../figg13/G1301749.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Engage Mainshaft Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">If not removing the upper reverse idler gear assembly, you must remove the upper
                    reverse idler gear assembly shaft and roll the gear to the outside. Refer to
                </emph>
                <hotlnk document="s13017_HL1301701.xml" xrefid="hl1301701">Reverse idler Gear Assembly</hotlnk>,
                <emph type="bold">, steps 1-4.</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the upper countershaft is not being removed, use a large screwdriver to block the upper
                countershaft assembly against the case wall (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301750">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301750" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301750" filename="../figg13/G1301750.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Rope Around Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">If removing the upper reverse idler gear assembly, refer to</emph>
                <hotlnk document="s13017_HL1301701.xml" xrefid="hl1301701">Reverse idler Gear Assembly</hotlnk>,
                <emph type="bold">, at this time.</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a hook or rope around the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301750">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the mainshaft to the rear to free the pilot from the input shaft pocket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt mainshaft front up and lift assembly from the case.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
